{
  "name": "Tele*",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"item-attunement\"><p><em>(Requires attunement by a spellcaster, unless they have another relic of the Hendecalyte.)</em></p></div><p>Found amongst a set of ruins in the area known as <em>The Choke</em>, this vortex-patterned, agate-like sphere, easily mistaken for a marble allows the spellcaster to manipulate teleportation and plane shifting-magics to an extraordinary degree.</p><p>While this relic is on your person, you gain a bonus to your initiative equal to the number of spells you have prepared that allow for teleportation, dimensional travel, plain shifting (or other similar spells, as the DM's discretion).</p><p>Furthermore, when you teleport, jaunt dimensions, plain shift (or other similar means of transportation, at the DM's discretion) yourself or other creatures you can wrap the energies around them to either protect or cause harm.</p><ul><li><strong>Abrupt Jaunt:</strong> A creature teleported by you suffers disadvantage on all ability checks, attack rolls, and saving throws until the end of their next turn.</li><li><strong>Teleshield:</strong> A creature teleported by you gains temporary hit points equal to your spellcasting ability modifier plus the spell's level.</li></ul><p>Lastly, the Tele acts as a dimensional anchor. Over the course of an hour, which can be done during periods of rest, the attuned can anchor themselves to their current plane of existence or demiplane. They treat the environment of the chosen plane as native for the purpose of overcoming negative environmental effects. Any attempt to remove the creature from said plane fails, unless the creature is willing.</p><p><strong>Spell Focus: </strong>A creature that has access to spellcasting can use this item as a spellcasting focus, as described in the <strong>Spellcasting</strong> section.</p><blockquote><p><strong>When you receive and attune to this item, you will need to update the Initiative Bonus effect on this item with the number of teleportation-related spells you have prepared.  You will need to continue updating this effect every time you make changes to your spell preparations as well.</strong></p></blockquote>",
